  "prompt": "How do I find an engine for an SAE Supra?",
  "response": "To find an engine for an SAE Supra, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Research Specifications**: Determine the exact engine requirements for the SAE Supra. This includes understanding the performance needs, compatibility, and regulations of the competition.\n\n2. **Contact Manufacturers or Sponsors**: Reach out to engine manufacturers or potential sponsors who may be interested in collaborating or providing engines for your project. Companies specializing in racing engines or those with a history in motorsports, such as Toyota Racing Development (TRD), Honda Performance Development (HPD), or other motorsport divisions, can be helpful.\n\n3. **Check Online Marketplaces and Forums**: Look at popular online marketplaces and forums like eBay Motors, Craigslist, and specialized forums for racing teams and enthusiasts. Websites like RacingJunk.com often have engines and parts for race cars.\n\n4. **Networking in the Motorsports Community**: Attend motorsport events and network with other teams, engineers, and suppliers. Establish connections with individuals who may have spare engines or know where you can find a compatible engine.\n\n5. **Visit Automotive and Racing Shops**: Local automotive and racing shops may have the expertise and resources to help you find the right engine. They may also have used or rebuilt engines that fit your needs.\n\n6. **Check University and College Resources**: Many universities and colleges involved in SAE competitions may have resources or partnerships that can help you find an engine. Speak to instructors, teams, or alumni for guidance.\n\n7. **Use Social Media and Online Communities**: Join social media groups, forums, and communities specific to SAE and motorsport enthusiasts. Post your requirements and seek advice or leads from fellow members.\n\n8. **Consider Rebuild Options**: If finding a complete engine is challenging, look for an engine that requires rebuilding. This can be a more cost-effective way to get the required engine specifications by rebuilding it to fit your needs.\n\nRemember that SAE competitions often have strict regulations, so ensure any engine you consider meets these standards.",
